    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA259-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu tōḻi talaimakaṉaic (EN, ER: talamakaḷaic) ceṟippaṟivuṟīi varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante urged for marriage, informing HIM about the confinement.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA259">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            yāṅkuccey vāṅko ṟōḻi poṉvī</l>
<l>            vēṅkai yōṅkiya tēṅkamaḻ cāraṟ</l>
<l>            peruṅka ṉāṭaṉō ṭirumpuṉat talkic</l>
<l>            cevvāyp paiṅkiḷi yōppi yavvāyp</l>
<l>            peruvarai yaṭukkat taruvi yāṭic </l>
<l>            cāra lāram vaṇṭupaṭa nīvip</l>
<l>            peritamarn tiyainta kēṇmaic ciṟunaṉi</l>
<l>            yariya pōlak kāṇpeṉ viritiraik</l>
<l>            kaṭalpeyarn taṉaiya vākip</l>
<l>            pularpataṅ koṇṭaṉa vēṉaṟ kuralē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>What do we do, friend?</l>
<l>I see they seem [to become] small [and] very rare,</l>
<l rend="indent2">the [moments of] intimacy, enjoyable [and] greatly desired,</l>
<l rend="indent">abiding in the vast fields with the man from the land of big stones,</l>
<l rend="indent2">on the slope fragrant with honey high with gold-blossomed Vēṅkai trees,</l>
<l rend="indent">scaring away the red-beaked green parakeets, playing</l>
<l rend="indent2">there in the waterfall on the big mountain side,</l>
<l rend="indent">smearing [on his/our chest] for bees to come sandal from the slope.</l>
<l rend="indent">Being as if the broad-waved sea had retreated,</l>
<l>the ears of the millet have taken [their] dry state.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
